### Problem Description

When using synthetic mode with nested fields, children fields may remain unloaded. This occurs when the fields present in the children docs are not uniform (e.g. when a child is missing a particular field).

### Steps to Reproduce

```

DELETE synthetic_test

# simple minimal mapping
PUT synthetic_test
{
    "mappings": {
        "properties": {
            "parent": {
                "type":"nested",
                "properties": {
                    "vector": {
                        "type": "dense_vector"
                    },
                    "text": {
                        "type": "text"
                    }
                }
            }
        }
    },
    "settings": {
    "index": {
      "mapping": {
        "source": {
          "mode": "synthetic"
        }
      }
    }
  }
}

PUT synthetic_test/_doc/0
{
    "parent": [{"vector": [1, 2],"text": "foo"}, {"vector": [2, 2], "text": "bar"}]
}

PUT synthetic_test/_doc/1
{
    "parent": [{"text": "foo"}, {"vector": [2, 2], "text": "bar"}]
}

PUT synthetic_test/_doc/2?refresh
{
    "parent": [{"vector": [1, 2]}, {"vector": [2, 2], "text": "bar"}]
}

GET synthetic_test/_search?size=20

```

Response is as follows (note how docs 1 and 2 are missing vectors in the response):

```
