### Problem Description

The highlighting throws an error or does not display correctly when a search is performed using the **unified** highlight type on a field containing **an array of texts**, and the search matches the end and beginning of two different phrases within the array:

Request:
```
GET error-case/_search
{
  "query": {
    "match_phrase": {
      "field1": {
        "query": "to be true the person"
      }
    }
  },
  "highlight": {
    "fields": {
      "field1": {
        "type": "unified"
      }
    }
  }
}
```

Response ERROR:
```
{
  "error": {
    "root_cause": [
      {
        "type": "illegal_state_exception",
        "reason": "first() should not be called in this context"
      }
    ],
    "type": "search_phase_execution_exception",
    "reason": "all shards failed",
    "phase": "query",
    "grouped": true,
    "failed_shards": [
      {
        "shard": 0,
        "index": "error-case",
        "node": "yooSs9yzSXCWHCpaxvpC_g",
        "reason": {
